    <h2 id="intro">Getting oriented</h2>
    <p>A typical help or information page has the same basic parts, shown here so that we are all familiar with, and use, the same terms: communication is so much easier if we all use the same term for the same part of the page!</p>

    <p class="push-half--bottom">The main parts of a page, from the top down, are the:</p>
    <ol>
      <li><strong>page header</strong>, which includes the:
        <ol style="list-style-type: upper-alpha;">
          <li>main navigation or site menu</li>
          <li>site logo</li>
        </ol>
      </li>
      <li>page <strong>main heading</strong> (<code>h1</code>)</li>
      <li><strong>leading paragraph</strong> — a brief summary of the page contents</li>
      <li>page <strong>contents</strong> </li>
      <li><strong>page sub-menu</strong> — table of contents</li>
      <li>other sub-menus (optional)</li>
      <li><strong>page footer</strong> </li>
    </ol>

