    <h3 id="theRefineryPanes">The two Refinery panes</h3>
    <p>When you open a page in Refinery, the preview pane (the text editing pane) is open. To see the HTML, select the ‘HTML’ button at the top of the preview pane. Select the button again to close the HTML pane.</p>
    <p class="islet islet--navy">Notice that I used the word ‘select’ rather than ‘click’: some of our users will not be able to click, because they are on a mobile device or they move around a page using only a keyboard. Writing ‘select’ is a good way to show such users that we have at least some understanding of their reality.</p>
    <p>The look of the content in the preview pane is very different from how the page will look in a browser: our CSS is not applied in Refinery. To see your page as it will appear to a user, select ‘Save’. Or, if you have used ‘Save and continue editing’, select ‘Pages’ (as in the menu shown top-left in <a href="#fig2">fig.&#160;2, above</a>). Find your page in the listing and select its right-most icon (which looks like an eye).</p>
    <p>The button next to the Save buttons, marked ‘Preview’ is not useful as it opens a browser tab where our CSS is not used.</p>
    <p>You can apply <em>some</em> markup from the preview pane — only a handful of elements and and none of our classes. For example, you can use the ‘I’ and ‘B’ buttons to apply the <code>em</code> and <code>strong</code> elements, respectively: select the text, then select the button.</p>
    <p>Please do <em>not</em> use the ‘Style’ button as it inserts classes that do not exist in our CSS!</p>
    <p>You’ll probably find it easier to add images from the preview pane, with the HTML pane closed — see <a href="#images">Images, below</a> for details.</p>
    <p>You'll also find it more convenient to add a link to another Refinery page from the preview pane: close the HTML pane, select the text in the preview pane that will be the link-text, then select the ‘Add link’ button. Now choose the type of link you need and select the one you are looking for.</p>
    <p>Please note that you will have to add in-page links and append id names to Refinery page addresses by hand, in the HTML pane.</p>
