    <h2 id="contentMarkup">Marking up the page contents</h2>
    <p>The single most important thing is to use <strong>semantic markup</strong>. This means marking up each piece of text with an element that matches its meaning or purpose rather than what it looks like in a browser. Our CSS will alter the appearance to fit with our brand style. (We could use more CSS to further change the appearance, if required and if the change is in keeping with the overall look of our pages — ask your manager for advice.) </p>
